cs.GT, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.DS, cs.MA 

This paper presents a model for decision making that generalizes Expected Utility Maximization, which is a fundamental concept in game theory (cs.GT), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also introduces the concept of nonstandard utilities, which can be seen as a type of data structure (cs.DS) used in decision making. Finally, the paper discusses the use of qualitative decision theory, which is a subfield of mathematical analysis (cs.MA) that deals with decision making under uncertainty.
